args:
The siblings are powerless before Alberius's
replica. Valyx expresses the admiration he'd
held for Alberius since childhood and attempts
to recruit him to their cause but receives a flat
refusal, leaving them no choice but to flee.
What? There's no way. He lived three\nhundred years ago!
No. That voice, that face... He's a bit\nyounger here, but it's just as I saw in the\nmemories at Clave Loy'elune. That's him.
Which means the real question is... Why?
Cast your newfound doubts aside. Be they\nhero of legend or my own blood ancestor,\nany who stand in my path shall fall!
A fine attack. But not enough to strike me\ndown, it seems.
That's not... That can't be... WHAT?! The\nmortal wound Leonidas dealt him healed\nin an instant!
That was... I see. So that's what this is.
If you've any insights, I would welcome an\nexplanation, brother.
I suspect that is one of the replicas yielded\nby the experiments I conducted back when\nI was a puppet of the Progenitor.
Experiments...? Why would you go and\nmake something like THAT?!
...I had my reasons. The want for a spare\npuppet to accept the Progenitor's will, for\none.
As a vessel able to contain that power, I\nrequired a replica fit to rival the original,\nboth physically and mentally.
Though it appears the Progenitor has used\nblack mana to warp its mind to better suit\nhis purposes...
And this replica is faithful enough it can\nshapeshift?
Yes. A feat achieved with mana modeled\nafter Alberius's own shapeshifting, as\nrecorded in memories of his battles.
It isn't true shapeshifting, strictly speaking,\nbut the results... The phenomena it creates\nare no less potent than the real thing.
Is such a thing even possible?
I was fortunate enough to get my hands on\nthe real thing, after all.
Correct. It was created from the remains\nof the Netherwyrm, merged into one with\nAlberius.
The Netherwyrm's... Alberius's remains.\nThen this truly is...
I set out to recreate the strongest person\nin recorded history, but in the end I\nabandoned the project.
Abandoned it? Then just what is that\nbefore us now, pray tell?
The experimental subject I had destroyed,\nI should guess. Repaired and awakened,\nsomehow.
I suspect we have the black mana's stirring\nin the wake of the Progenitor's return to\nthank for its awakening.
Still, I had never thought to encounter it\nlike this. ...It's a bitter fruit my efforts have\nsown. The responsibility for this is mine.
Sorry, were you about done talking? I'd\nlike to continue, unless you wanted to just\nsurrender now?
Really, now. An attack like that won't stop\nme?
This isn't good... Brother, does the replica\nhave some weakness? Surely there's some\nsort of countermeasure?
That replica was born of all the world's\nmemories of Alberius, preserved in each\nof its mana spots.
As I said, it is a mental and physical match\nfor the real Alberius. What's more, it can't\nbe hurt in the presence of black mana.
That's unreasonable! How are we meant to\nbeat a monster like that?!
However... It holds a core that sustains and\ncontrols it. Were we able to strike that\ncore, somehow...
Where will we find this core?
The left breast, like to the seat of a man's\nheart. If destroyed, the replica will be\nunable to maintain its form and fall apart.
You're quick to optimism. We're up against\nAlberius, hero of legend. Just fighting him\nat all is a tall order.
I don't see what other choice we have...\nCome, let's join Leonidas!
Just lovely... Come along, then. No\ndawdling.
You've brawn fit to rival a rokkan. But an\nattack that doesn't connect is no threat!
No... All of them together, and it STILL\nwasn't enough?
That just leaves you. ...Are you just going\nto stand there?
Rgh... I won't be made a fool of! R-...\nRAAAAAAH!
*sigh*... That was just sad. Maybe in\nanother 300 years, kid.
Damn you... Don't think this is over...\nWe're not out of this yet!
No, you've definitely lost. And this world is\nat its end.
That capacity to surpass your limits when\nprotecting another... You truly are\nAlberius's descendants.
You speak as if you really did have his\nmemories inside you...
Oh, I do. I've learned it all. ...Perhaps it's\nmore accurate to say I know it.
His travels with the Windwyrm. The battle\nwith the Other. The founding of a kingdom\nwhere man and dragon could coexist...
I know everything that made Alberius the\nman he was. And what of it?
...When I was a boy, I loved listening to\nthe tales of Alberius. I idolized him.\nDreamt of becoming a man in his image.
The undefeated warrior, vanquisher of the\nOther. Proud king and founder of Alberia.\nHero who fought alone for his people...
If you truly carry his memories and will\ninside you, how can you stand on that side\nof this battle?! It's not too late to join us!
Trying to talk me into defecting? Awfully\nconniving, for a man who looks like a\nwalking slab of muscle.
That isn't my intention! I merely don't want\nto see the noble ideals Alberius once held\ndragged through the mud byâ€”
Noble ideals? What are you on about? I\ndon't know what legends they filled your\nhead with, but you understand nothing.
I may only be a copy, but I hold the real\nAlberius's memories within me. So let me\nshare the truth with you.
Alberius was just a man who happened to\nswing a sword a bit better than most.\nUndefeated? Hah. He lost plenty of battles.
He didn't become king because he wanted\nto, so he didn't feel a speck of pride about\nit. And he fought alone out of convenience.
The hero you idolized is a false idol, made\nby centuries of brazenly embellished tales.\nAlberius was not the man you think him.
He just wanted to enjoy life. There was no\nlofty ideal or grand purpose there. Don't go\nprojecting your own desires on others!
I shall treat your wounds immediately,\nValyx!
Are you Alberian royals too, then? ...More\nof Alberius's descendants?
Is... Is that Alberius? But, how?
It's a replica. I'll skip the details for now,\nbut it's clearly not him. That thing you see\nis our enemy.
She's quite right. My flesh and mind may\nbe recreations of Alberius's, but we are not\nthe same.
I am not a hero who would fight to thwart\nthe Other, nor am I Alberia's king.
I am an existence whose purpose has been\ndetermined... To destroy you, and quash all\npossibility from this world with this power!
So you claim to hold no free will or choice\nwithin you. A puppet whose possibilities\nhave been stolen by the Progenitor, then!
Rgh, he's strong... But this is a fight we\ncannot lose! Dragons, grant me your might!\nHAAAAAAAH!
Shapeshifting... Then I too will show you\nthe power of the dragonblood!
Brother, you can't! If you move in your\ncondition, you'll tear your wound back\nopen!
Fighting in that state is a losing\nproposition. Judging from the situation,\nwe need to fall back and regroup.
Retreat?! And what, hole up inside the\nHalidom?!
I doubt that's possible. I saw an army of\nfiends advancing in the Halidom's direction\na short while ago.
If we retreat in that direction, we'll be\ncaught between this thing and them before\nwe reach the castle. ...We won't survive it.
Okay, so what DO we do, then?!
Oh ho. Another multiple pact holder? Then\nI'll have to stay on my toes!
I don't need you to tell me!
We've no choice. We're abandoning the\nHalidom!
Slipped away, have they? ...No matter. My\nimmediate goals are accomplished. And\nbesides, we'll meet again soon enough.
